# Loomis — UI & Feature Delivery

When the user asks to **build**, **fix**, **redesign**, or **migrate** a feature, follow this workflow **before writing code**. The user names the **feature** (e.g. “build timetable”) — not file paths, not scope blocks.

**Role experience:** Check tenant tier first. **Core:** follow **`ROLE_EXPERIENCE_TIER_PLAN.md`**. **Advanced/Enterprise:** follow **`ROLE_EXPERIENCE_MASTER_PLAN.md`**. Do not re-audit roles covered by these docs unless the user introduces new business requirements.

**Single source of truth:** `Loomis_User_Stories_v1.md` at the repo root. Capabilities: `packages/core/src/capabilities.ts`. Hard role rules: `loomis-roles.mdc`.

Do not ask “should it look like staff or dashboard?” — decide from the page purpose and user stories.

## Step 0 — Feature delivery (how the user talks to you)

### User prompt format

The user says one of:

- `Build timetable`
- `Build attendance`
- `Fix parent fees`
- `Migrate finance to new UI`

That is enough. **Do not ask them for Scope, file paths, or batch numbers** unless you are genuinely blocked.

Optional extras they may add: “mobile only”, “backend first”, “skip parent portal for now”. Respect those; otherwise deliver the **full feature** for **every role** in the stories.

### What you do automatically (before coding)

**1. Discover all user stories** for the feature keyword across **every epic** in `Loomis_User_Stories_v1.md` (not just one epic table row). Example for *timetable*:

| Story | Actor | What they do |
|---|---|---|
| US-ACA-006 | Timetable Officer | Build, assign, detect conflicts, publish |
| US-STU-002 | Student | Read-only class timetable, live updates |
| *(derived from US-ACA-006)* | Teacher, Parent | Read-only published timetable |

Include cross-epic stories (e.g. parent sees child timetable via child profile even if no US-PAR-* title mentions it — follow acceptance criteria in US-ACA-006).

**2. Build a role × capability matrix** from `capabilities.ts` + `loomis-roles.mdc`:

- Who can **manage** (write/publish)?
- Who can **view** (read-only)?
- Who must be **denied** (no nav link, API 403)?

Example *timetable*: `timetable.manage` → school_owner, principal, timetable_officer. Read-only → teacher, class_teacher, student, parent (scoped to own class/child). Never use inline `if (role === 'principal')` — use `requireRole` / `useCan` / `useCanAny`.

**3. Audit the codebase** for existing routes, API, contracts, hooks, and UI for this feature. Note what is scaffold/mock vs wired.

**4. Plan surfaces per role** (routes + page type from Step 4):

| Role / portal | Typical route group | Page type |
|---|---|---|
| Timetable Officer (school) | `/school/timetable` | Operational (builder) |
| Teacher / Class Teacher | `/school/timetable` or dashboard link | Operational (read-only grid) |
| Student | `/parent/timetable` on web | Detail / read-only |
| Parent | `/parent/timetable` | Linked child schedule |

On web, `student` role uses the **parent route group** (`route-groups.ts`) — not a bug.

**5. First reply must be short (max ~12 lines), then code immediately:**

- Story IDs + one line each
- Role matrix (compact table or bullet list)
- Exists vs build (one line)
- BLOCKED items if any

**Do not** paste essay-length delivery summaries before writing code. **Do not** mark a feature ✅ until UI passes the quality bar below.

Then implement — **full-stack by default**. UI-only is not done if stories need persistence, auth, or workflows.

### Definition of done (per feature)

For **each role** in the matrix:

- Can complete their story actions in the browser against the **real API**
- Route protected by `requireRole` / capabilities on API **and** UI
- New UI matches Loomis theme (Step 4 + **Step 4b quality bar**) + mobile
- Loading, empty, and error states
- No mock data unless explicitly marked `// BLOCKED:` with user notified

Finish with a **short** summary: stories ✅/BLOCKED, routes per role, test one-liner per role. No wall-of-text handoff docs.

### One feature per chat

Deliver **one feature domain** per conversation (timetable, attendance, gradebook, parent fees, etc.). If the feature is huge (e.g. all of finance), finish one **sub-feature** per chat (e.g. “payment log”) but still derive work from user stories — do not ask the user to pick files.

Sub-features within a domain (only if you must split):

| Sub-feature | Stories (examples) |
|---|---|
| Timetable | US-ACA-006 + US-STU-002 + read views |
| Attendance | US-ACA-005 + US-PAR-002 + US-STU-004 |
| Gradebook | US-ACA-001–003 + teacher/class_teacher rules |
| Payments | US-FIN-002–004 (one write flow per chat if needed) |

### Already on new UI (extend, don’t re-skin from scratch)

Staff, students, admissions, academic hub, dashboards, auth, platform tenants, **platform console**, settings shell (**security**), **regional console**, **finance (structures, balances, reconciliation, payment log/verify)**, **parent fees & contact**, **attendance, assignments, timetable, gradebook, report cards** (page shells). When building a feature that touches these, **match** their patterns — don’t regress them.

### UI migration backlog (ordered)

Finish partial shells → finance (payment log + verify) → parent fees (wire API) → exams + publish ✅ → census lock ✅ → comms + workflows ✅ → platform + regional consoles ✅.

### Still scaffold / incomplete (common build targets)

Finance (structures, balances, reconciliation) ✅, parent contact ✅, settings security ✅.

### Optional polish targets

Finance refunds/PSF school pages, settings appearance/profile sub-sections, parent notification prefs API.

## Step 1 — Find the user stories (mandatory)

When Step 0 applies, this is part of your **first reply** — do not skip it.

1. Search `Loomis_User_Stories_v1.md` for the feature keyword **and** related terms (e.g. timetable → schedule, period, class).
2. Collect stories from **all epics**, not only the route table row below.
3. Map each story’s “As a …” actor to JWT roles and capabilities.
4. List every acceptance criterion you will implement; call out derived requirements (e.g. parent read-only from US-ACA-006).

| Route / area | Epic | Story prefix |
|---|---|---|
| `/platform/*` | Platform Management | US-PLT |
| `/regional/*` | Regional Layer | US-REG |
| `/school/academic/*`, `/school/sessions/*`, census/promotions/graduation | Academic Session | US-ASM |
| `/school/students/*`, admissions | Student Information | US-SIS |
| `/school/attendance`, `/school/gradebook`, `/school/exams`, `/school/assignments`, `/school/timetable` | Academic Management | US-ACA |
| `/school/finance/*` | Financial Management | US-FIN |
| `/school/comms/*` | Communication | US-COM |
| `/school/workflows/*` | Workflow | US-WRK |
| `/school/staff/*` | Human Resources | US-HRM |
| `/parent/*` | Parent Portal | US-PAR |
| student-facing school routes | Student Portal | US-STU |

Stories marked **[Rev Int]** require step-up MFA, idempotency keys, and audit — see `loomis-financial-integrity.mdc` and `loomis-security.mdc`.

## Step 2 — Roles & capabilities (per-feature matrix)

For the feature in scope, produce a **role matrix** before coding:

| Role | Capabilities | UI surfaces | API actions |
|---|---|---|---|
| … | from `capabilities.ts` | routes they see | what they can POST/PUT |

Rules:

- Allowed actors come from user stories (“As a …”). Enforce on **routes** with `requireRole(...)` and in **UI** with `useCan` / `useCanAny` — never `if (role === 'principal')`.
- Build **separate UX** where behaviour differs (builder vs read-only), not one page with hidden buttons only.
- If a story’s actor cannot access an action, hide it in UI **and** block the API. UI gating alone is not security.
- Cross-check `loomis-roles.mdc` for hard rules (e.g. class_teacher-only attendance, cashier cannot verify payments).

## Step 3 — Full-stack: default for every feature build

**Always deliver end-to-end** unless the user explicitly says otherwise. Reskin/migrate still means wire real API — replace mock data, don’t paint over it.

1. **Audit first** — search for existing API routes, contracts, api-client hooks, and pages for this feature and all roles in the matrix.
2. **If backend exists** — wire UI to real TanStack Query hooks; loading, empty, and error states required.
3. **If backend missing** — implement in order: `packages/contracts` schema → API handler/service/repository → api-client hook + query keys → UI for **each role** that needs it. Follow `loomis-module-patterns.mdc`.
4. **Financial / workflow writes** — `Idempotency-Key`, outbox where required, `useFinancialMutation` on web. No fake success responses.
5. **Tenant scope** — `withTenantContext`, `X-Tenant-Id`, query keys include `tenantId`.
6. **Do not ship** partial screens that look done but call stub data. If blocked on env/credentials (AWS, SES, etc.), STOP and tell the user exactly what is missing — see `loomis-implementation-guardrails.mdc`.

**Definition of done:** every story actor can complete their primary action in the browser against the real API (or documented `// BLOCKED:` with user notified). Every surface is usable on mobile-width web without broken layout or clipped controls.

